         <entry xml:id="Games_Lewisvariousgames-d0e168">
            <form>
               <orth>speilipan</orth>
            </form>
            <def>See attached slip. [NOTES: the following copied from the attached piece of paper.] L – Lever, which was hit with a bat, cromag [?] stave etc., which flung the ball into the air. From then the game was similar to cluich air house i.e. rounders. When the players were few, the catcher had the privilege of wielding the bat. There was quite an art in playing the ball in the hole: central, or to the left slightly or to the right slightly depending on how the field was set. Also the wielding of the bat gave room for the display of skill. Hit for 4, hit for 6 or interval for trot.
        <graphic url="Lewisvariousgamesillust2.jpg" width="300px"/>
